65
00:06:26,890 --> 00:06:29,430
I still haven't decided yet.

66
00:06:30,620 --> 00:06:33,130
Is that so?

67
00:07:25,630 --> 00:07:27,350
Want some water?

68
00:07:29,050 --> 00:07:30,570
Yeah.

69
00:07:56,520 --> 00:07:58,210
- Thanks.
- Sure.

70
00:08:08,660 --> 00:08:13,550
<i>Both of us avoid the most important topic.</i>

71
00:08:18,090 --> 00:08:23,980
I feel you. Divorce is the slowest-moving topic in the world to start talking about.

72
00:08:23,980 --> 00:08:28,500
In my mind, I know very well that we need to talk about it.

73
00:08:28,500 --> 00:08:31,460
That's easier said than done.

74
00:08:32,350 --> 00:08:35,340
I can't live with my wife anymore.

75
00:08:35,340 --> 00:08:38,980
But I don't want to leave Shiori either.

76
00:08:38,980 --> 00:08:43,590
And I don't want to tear my wife and Shiori apart.

77
00:08:44,500 --> 00:08:47,150
This is really tangled up.

78
00:08:47,150 --> 00:08:50,170
So, all I can do is cut off the ties.

79
00:08:50,170 --> 00:08:53,300
My ties to them, that is.

80
00:08:53,300 --> 00:08:56,060
So, you're the only one leaving?

81
00:08:57,360 --> 00:09:00,400
The only solution I can think of is for me to pull back.

82
00:09:02,230 --> 00:09:05,120
The choice is up to you.

83
00:09:05,590 --> 00:09:10,550
But even if you're divorced, you'll still be your daughter's father.

84
00:09:10,550 --> 00:09:15,430
Just make sure that you can still get to see her, share custody, and...

85
00:09:16,270 --> 00:09:19,450
It still boils down to having a discussion, right?

86
00:09:19,450 --> 00:09:23,440
Regardless of how it turns out, it's the end for me once we're divorced.

87
00:09:23,950 --> 00:09:26,240
Why is it the end for you?

88
00:09:26,240 --> 00:09:28,120
Why?

89
00:09:29,640 --> 00:09:32,560
We're not related by blood, that's why.

90
00:09:32,560 --> 00:09:34,690
You know that.

91
00:09:34,690 --> 00:09:37,390
Come on, dude.

92
00:09:37,390 --> 00:09:41,950
You're leaving because you and your daughter aren't biologically related?

93
00:09:43,100 --> 00:09:45,520
She isn't my child.

94
00:09:46,390 --> 00:09:48,850
Can you bring yourself to say that to Shiori-chan?

95
00:09:51,310 --> 00:09:55,290
You can probably say that to your wife, or to yourself,

96
00:09:55,290 --> 00:09:57,770
but can you say that to Shiori-chan?

97
00:09:59,050 --> 00:10:01,330
Can you look Shiori-chan in the eye and say,

98
00:10:01,330 --> 00:10:04,760
"You are not my child"?

99
00:10:07,370 --> 00:10:09,570
Are you really sure you can say that to her?

100
00:10:13,500 --> 00:10:17,140
How does Shiori-chan behave when she sees you?

101
00:10:18,190 --> 00:10:20,740
She smiles, doesn't she?

102
00:10:22,980 --> 00:10:25,270
When you carry her,

103
00:10:25,270 --> 00:10:30,940
will she recognize your smell and calm down before falling asleep?

104
00:10:33,050 --> 00:10:35,230
Isn't it the same for you?

105
00:10:35,230 --> 00:10:40,850
Won't smelling Shiori-chan calm you down as well?

106
00:10:42,060 --> 00:10:46,140
You said before that you're the best at giving her baths, right?

107
00:10:47,890 --> 00:10:50,300
That, my friend...

108
00:10:52,840 --> 00:10:56,160
