180
00:17:00,040 --> 00:17:02,280
You're fine with not knowing who he is?

181
00:17:02,280 --> 00:17:06,510
If I knew his identity, I'd probably wanna beat him up.

182
00:17:06,510 --> 00:17:08,840
That's why I won't want to meet him.

183
00:17:08,840 --> 00:17:11,220
I don't think you'll do something like that, though.

184
00:17:11,220 --> 00:17:15,660
But it'll just keep bugging me.

185
00:17:15,660 --> 00:17:17,580
You can't move on, right?

186
00:17:17,580 --> 00:17:22,610
Yes, I won't be able to find closure if things remain like this.

187
00:17:24,510 --> 00:17:30,020
It's not that you want to know who that man is.

188
00:17:30,020 --> 00:17:33,800
You want to know what your wife is thinking, don't you?

189
00:17:35,970 --> 00:17:39,600
What is your wife trying to protect?

190
00:17:39,600 --> 00:17:42,520
Why is she trying to protect him?

191
00:17:42,520 --> 00:17:46,260
These questions have been bogging you down.

192
00:17:47,460 --> 00:17:50,060
That's the reason you can't move on.

193
00:17:52,310 --> 00:17:53,860
Am I right?

194
00:18:32,820 --> 00:18:34,750
Hiroki?

195
00:18:38,520 --> 00:18:41,250
- Hiroki.
- Sorry.

196
00:18:41,890 --> 00:18:43,780
Are you okay?

197
00:19:50,580 --> 00:19:54,070
Fuyutsuki, I see that you've properly moved on, right?

198
00:19:56,430 --> 00:19:59,740
I should find something I want to do, too.

199
00:20:05,520 --> 00:20:07,020
Want coffee?

200
00:20:07,020 --> 00:20:08,480
Sure.

201
00:20:09,270 --> 00:20:12,430
- Wait, I'll do it.
- Let me do it.

202
00:20:14,620 --> 00:20:16,300
Thanks.

203
00:20:29,690 --> 00:20:31,960
As expected.

204
00:20:32,800 --> 00:20:36,220
You'll just start from scratch again if you fail, right?

205
00:20:38,640 --> 00:20:40,750
Wise words indeed.

206
00:20:40,750 --> 00:20:43,090
That's so like you, Fuyutsuki.

207
00:20:46,470 --> 00:20:52,240
There were some words that inspired me to start this business.

208
00:20:52,240 --> 00:20:54,730
I just rephrased it a little.

209
00:20:54,730 --> 00:20:56,200
What?

210
00:20:56,200 --> 00:20:59,110
Even if we have to give up our dreams and goals,

211
00:20:59,110 --> 00:21:02,510
there are still plenty of wonderful things in this world.

212
00:21:02,510 --> 00:21:05,040
It's just that we haven't discovered them yet.

213
00:21:07,360 --> 00:21:11,460
That's how I got the phrase, "We'll start from scratch again if we fail."

214
00:21:13,530 --> 00:21:18,540
Because there are still many things in this world that we haven't discovered yet.

215
00:21:24,080 --> 00:21:29,850
Were those words from that person who's important to you?

216
00:21:30,520 --> 00:21:31,990
Yeah.

217
00:21:35,320 --> 00:21:39,940
So, I'm sure you'll find something that you want to do, Risa.

218
00:21:52,740 --> 00:21:55,190
What kind of person is she?

219
00:22:01,120 --> 00:22:03,020
Okay...

220
00:22:04,240 --> 00:22:07,150
What are you doing?

221
00:22:07,740 --> 00:22:11,320
What's that? A letter?

222
00:22:11,320 --> 00:22:12,960
Yes, it is.

223
00:22:13,520 --> 00:22:17,900
Inside this letter is a string of precious words.

224
00:22:17,900 --> 00:22:19,060
Read it.

225
00:22:19,060 --> 00:22:21,480
What? No, we can't.

226
00:22:21,480 --> 00:22:25,660
Kota, we aren't supposed to read other people's letters without permission, you hear?

227
00:22:25,660 --> 00:22:28,070
Why not?

228
00:22:29,380 --> 00:22:34,390
Because the precious feelings of the writer are enclosed inside.

229
00:22:34,390 --> 00:22:38,350
Only the letter's recipient is allowed to read it.

230
00:22:40,280 --> 00:22:43,030
Is it a love letter?

231
00:22:43,690 --> 00:22:46,270
Every letter is a love letter.

232
00:22:46,270 --> 00:22:52,930
Besides, it has been properly received by that person.

233
00:22:53,800 --> 00:22:56,050
There's no need for it anymore.

234
00:23:25,550 --> 00:23:29,870
<i>Good day. This is Kanzaki from Mitsukura Corporation.</i>

235
00:23:29,870 --> 00:23:33,980
<i>I'm dropping you an email to reschedule our appointment.</i>

236
00:23:33,980 --> 00:23:37,010
<i>I sincerely apologize for any inconvenience caused,</i>

237
00:23:37,010 --> 00:23:40,190
<i>and thank you for your consideration.</i>

238
00:23:40,190 --> 00:23:42,160
<i>Postscript.</i>

239
00:23:42,160 --> 00:23:47,730
<i>Thanks to Fuyutsuki-sama's help, I was able to swiftly bring my child to the hospital.</i>

240
00:23:47,730 --> 00:23:52,160
<i>I greatly appreciate your thoughtfulness.</i>

241
00:23:58,580 --> 00:23:59,780
Hello?

242
00:23:59,780 --> 00:24:02,440
Hello, I apologize for the sudden call.

243
00:24:02,440 --> 00:24:04,790
This is Mizuki from Tri Ambition.

244
00:24:04,790 --> 00:24:07,620
Oh, I sent you an email not long ago.

245
00:24:07,620 --> 00:24:11,790
<i>The reason for my call is not regarding the financing.</i>

246
00:24:11,790 --> 00:24:15,450
Kanzaki-san, I wish to ask you for a favor.

247
00:24:15,450 --> 00:24:17,210
<i>What is it?</i>

248
00:24:17,210 --> 00:24:21,730
Our company is planning to organize another flea market.

249
00:24:21,730 --> 00:24:24,620
Flea market? The one you did at the library?

250
00:24:24,620 --> 00:24:25,870
<i>That's right.</i>

251
